main event: On October 31st, 1950, a civilian pilot and engineers reported an aluminum object with a blue flame over Cuba, flying faster than a meteor at an altitude of over 5,000 feet for a duration of 3 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as circular and of terrific size.
No photographs or sketches of the object were included with the report.
The speed of the object was noted to be faster than a meteor, indicating unusual behavior.
The report indicates that there were multiple sightings of unidentified aerial objects in Cuba around the same time.
There was uncertainty about the authenticity of pictures of the unidentified aerial objects.
sighted object: aluminum object with a blue flame
